{
  "texts": [
    "Case 2: Clean slate, products without legacy This is well-suited to S2-S4 due to the absence of outdated architectures and languages.",
    "AI tools can be fully leveraged for a broad spectrum of tasks e.g., code generation, debugging, testing, deployment, and maintenance.",
    "For larger software operations, S2 is more likely to occur in the short-to mid-term, as AI is increasingly being used in automating repetitive and even customer (DevOps) facing tasks.",
    "For simpler applications, we see many offers with zero-and no-code environments, or code generation services.",
    "In the long term, S3 and later S4 are more likely as AI tools and their integration into processes matures."
  ]
}